Mike Hebert.label: Mike Hebert
Mike Hebert.description:
Mike Hebert is a retired American volleyball coach.
He coached since 1976 and in his career, he coached Pittsburgh men and women's team, New Mexico women's team, Illinois women's team, and Minnesota women's team. Wikipedia

Julio Velasco.label: Julio Velasco
Julio Velasco.description: Julio Velasco is a professional volleyball coach from Argentina, who guided the Italian national men's team to several successes in the 1990s. After the 1996 Summer Olympics, where the Italians won silver, he switched to the Italian women's team. Wikipedia

Bernardo Rezende.label: Bernardo Rezende
Bernardo Rezende.description: Bernardo Rocha de Rezende known as Bernardinho is a Brazilian volleyball coach and former volleyball player. He is the current coach of both Brazil men's national volleyball team and the female volleyball team Rio de Janeiro Vôlei Clube. Wikipedia
Bernardo Rezende.Born: May 28, 1959 (age 54), Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil

Michael Sealy.label: Michael Sealy
Michael Sealy.description: Michael Sealy is an American volleyball coach. He is the head coach of the women's volleyball team at UCLA. He was named on February 10, 2010 to succeed Andy Banachowski who announced his retirement after 43 years. Wikipedia

John Speraw.label: John Speraw
John Speraw.description: John Speraw, is an American volleyball coach. He is the head coach of the men's volleyball team at UCLA and United states national olympic volleyball team assistant coach. Wikipedia

Harlan Cohen.label: Harlan Cohen
Harlan Cohen.description: Harlan Cohen is an American volleyball coach who led both the United States men's and women's national teams during the mid-1960s. Cohen coached the men in 1966. Wikipedia

Doug Beal.label: Doug Beal
Doug Beal.description: Doug Beal is an American volleyball player and coach, the current USA Volleyball CEO, and a member of the International Jewish Sports Hall of Fame. Wikipedia

Mick Haley.label: Mick Haley
Mick Haley.description: Mick Haley is an American volleyball coach. Currently, he is the head coach of the University of Southern California women's volleyball team. He has also coached the U.S. Women's National Team at the Olympics. Wikipedia

Stelian Moculescu.label: Stelian Moculescu
Stelian Moculescu.description: Stelian Moculescu is a Romanian volleyball coach and former player. He is currently the head coach of VfB Friedrichshafen. From 1987 to 1990 and from 1999 to 2008 he was also the coach of the Germany men's national volleyball team. Wikipedia

Jim McLaughlin (coach).label: Jim McLaughlin
Jim McLaughlin (coach).description: Jim McLaughlin is an American volleyball coach. He just completed his 13th season as Head Coach for the University of Washington Women's Volleyball team. Wikipedia

Jan De Brandt.label: Jan De Brandt
Jan De Brandt.description: Jan De Brandt is a Belgian former volleyball player and current free agent coach. He last coached for Igtisadchi Baku for 2010-11 season. Wikipedia

Violet Duca.label: Violet Duca
Violet Duca.description: Violet Kostanda Duca is a Turkish former volleyball player and current Fenerbahçe Acıbadem manager. She is Greek descent. Her father Hristo Kostanda is a former footballer and played for Beşiktaş JK. She played 120 times for national team. . Wikipedia

Pete Waite.label: Pete Waite
Pete Waite.description: William Peter Waite is an American volleyball coach and author, and is a former head coach for the women's volleyball team at Wisconsin. Wikipedia

Arnie Ball.label: Arnie Ball
Arnie Ball.description: Armond J. "Arnie" Ball began his 30th season in 2010 as the head coach of the IPFW Men's Mastodon volleyball program. Coach Ball has established a legacy on the courts of both the Mastodons and the national scenes. Wikipedia

Cecile Reynaud.label: Cecile Reynaud
Cecile Reynaud.description: Dr. Cecile Reynaud is a well-known volleyball educator and a retired coach of the Florida State Lady Seminoles volleyball team. She is currently an associate professor with the sport management program at Florida State University. Wikipedia
Cecile Reynaud.Born: August 7, 1953 (age 60), Webster Groves, Missouri, United States

Andy Banachowski.label: Andy Banachowski
Andy Banachowski.description: John Andrew Banachowski is an American volleyball coach. He was the head coach of the women's volleyball team at UCLA. Wikipedia

Daniele Bagnoli.label: Daniele Bagnoli
Daniele Bagnoli.description: Daniele Bagnoli is an Italian volleyball coach of Iran powerhouse Matin Varamin VC.He was assistant coach for Italy men's national volleyball team and coached Russia men's national volleyball team. Wikipedia

Sergei Ovchinnikov (volleyball).label: Sergei Ovchinnikov
Sergei Ovchinnikov (volleyball).description: Sergei Anatolyevich Ovchinnikov was the head coach of the Russia's National Women Volleyball Team. He committed suicide three weeks after the team lost to Brazil at the 2012 Summer Olympics quarterfinals. Wikipedia
